    &lt;Title&gt;Brilliant Service &lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I attended the Endoscopy unit on a 2WW referral. My first appointment with the sister for a ‘pre-op” was fantastic, she set my mind at ease explained the process and how to use the prep in details she told me what to expect and what to look out for. I then got an appointment for my procedure. I was very nervous and ended with not eating and drinking and the nerves I ended up passing out! The nursing team were fantastic, I was very embarrassed but they were so reassuring and calm they checked in my every couple of minutes to make sure I was ok and generally keep me updated with what was happening, waiting times etc. I have to say from admin staff, nurses and consultants, I could not have had better care and compassion. What was a nerve wrecking, uncomfortable and embarrassing procedure I can honestly say I was treated with such respect and dignity that I would highly recommend this hospital! Thank you to all the staff involved in my care.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
